Review of Trung Nguyen Coffee - Remax: Disappointment after upgrading  I have been a regular customer of Trung Nguyen Coffee - Remax for more than half a year, especially love the egg meat sandwich with coffee at a reasonable combo price of 55,000 VND. However, after the restaurant was upgraded, my experience completely changed in a negative direction. Disappointing points: * Price hike: The price of a single egg shumai sandwich has increased to 66,000 VND, a price too high compared to the quality received. * Food quality has decreased: The taste of egg shumai bread is no longer as good as before, far behind the Remax Coffee shop next door with a more affordable price (45,000 VND). * Noisy space: Using a lot of glass in the design makes the shop very noisy, especially when there are many customers. The chatter of groups of customers creates a bustling feeling like a market, losing the inherent quietness of a coffee shop.  * Inadequate upgrades: Although the restaurant space is more beautiful and luxurious after the upgrade, these changes cannot compensate for the decrease in food quality and increase in prices.  Conclude: With the current price and quality of food like that, I will never return to Trung Nguyen Coffee - Remax again. I feel disappointed by this negative change.

On the evening of February 9, 2025, I and my younger brother just went drinking here. And I still get served as always, the atmosphere and decoration of the restaurant have been upgraded very beautifully!!! But when the iced tea was brought out, everything beautiful in my eyes was Shattered!!!! The iced tea has a very disgusting taste!!! It smells of tobacco, very strong, I don't believe that a reputable cafe like Trung Nguyen would use such disgusting iced tea to invite customers to drink... It didn't stop there, I drank a cotton ball the size of a cigarette filter. I still didn't believe this was a cigarette filter, so I showed it to the barista. They didn't explain and didn't apologize for the cotton ball, and just said that the tea smelled similar to cigarettes, because I couldn't remember what kind of tea we were using. And I asked for a new glass of iced tea, but it still smelled like cigarettes, very disgusting!!! After returning home, I recalled the incident. I deduced that a cigarette had been dropped in that batch of tea, cooked, and given to customers to drink without the shop's carelessness. Right now I'm still having chills and vomiting from the horrible taste of that iced tea!!! This is my own opinion, it may be right or wrong, but the cotton ball in the tea cup is very unusual. Sincerely give your feedback so that the shop can fix it if it was accidentally dropped in, or if it's really due to the smell of that tea, please change to another type, because I'm sure no one can drink tea that smells 100% like tobacco!!!
